[SDG-WAYSHELL-CONFIGS]: Volume OSD appears when cursor touches the right screen edge — shows volume level, mute state, and supports scroll/click adjustment.
[SDG-WAYSHELL-CONFIGS]: Brightness OSD appears when cursor touches the left screen edge — mirror of volume OSD using brightnessctl.
[SDG-WAYSHELL-CONFIGS]: Screenshot toolbar appears at top-center — capture monitor, area, all monitors, or window; cycle between disk/clipboard/editor output modes.
[SDG-WAYSHELL-CONFIGS]: Elevated process bar (bottom-left) shows sudo/root processes running on any monitor — click to focus a process window.
[SDG-WAYSHELL-CONFIGS]: Focused process bar (bottom-right) shows the active window's CPU per-core, RAM, and GPU (nvidia-smi) usage in real time.
[SDG-WAYSHELL-CONFIGS]: Monocle switchers show per-monitor window lists when monocle/deck/vdeck layout is active — up to 10 slots per monitor with click-to-focus.
